{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"curly-tally-trench","description":"## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. Pick a bound ticket with 0 comments on both sides (e.g. REB-5 / local\n   0241-c6c1-0a20-491b).\n2. Add a LOCAL comment: `rebar comment <local_id> \"local-origin\"`.\n3. Add a JIRA comment to the same issue: `acli jira workitem comment create\n   --key <REB-N> --body \"jira-origin\"`.\n4. Run a reconcile pass (`rebar reconcile --mode live`).\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n\n- **Expected:** bidirectional, additive comment sync — both sides end with BOTH\n  comments (2 in Jira, 2 in local).\n- **Actual:** **Jira = 2 (outbound works), local = 1 (inbound BROKEN).** The\n  Jira-origin comment is never mirrored to local. `RECON: inbound_differ total=N\n  with_comments=0` — zero inbound comment imports, fleet-wide (not just this ticket).\n\n## Root cause (confirmed in code)\n\n- `inbound_differ.compute_inbound_mutations(jira_snapshot, binding_store,\n  local_by_id, outbound_mutations)` takes **no client**.\n- `inbound_differ._diff_comments_inbound(jira_fields, local_ticket)` reads comments\n  from `jira_fields[\"comment\"]` — but the live **search snapshot does NOT include\n  comment data** (Jira search omits comments; documented in `outbound_differ`). So the\n  inbound differ sees 0 Jira comments and imports none.\n- The OUTBOUND differ DOES fetch comments (`client.get_comments`, for dedup) but that\n  fetched data is not shared with the inbound path. So outbound comment sync works and\n  inbound does not.\n\n## Fix approach\n\nGive the inbound comment path the Jira comments — e.g. (a) thread the outbound\ndiffer's already-fetched comments into the inbound snapshot/`compute_inbound_mutations`,\nor (b) pass a client to `compute_inbound_mutations` so `_diff_comments_inbound` can\nfetch via `get_comments` (bounded, mirroring the outbound path), or (c) include comment\ndata on the snapshot entries the inbound differ sees (reuse the absent-alive GET path).\nOutbound comments carry the `<!-- rebar:reconciler-echo -->` marker and dedup is by\n`jira_comment_id`, so our own echoes are already filtered — the fix must not re-import\nlocally-originated comments.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A comment created directly in Jira (no reconciler marker, not already in local)\n      is mirrored inbound as a local comment on the next pass.\n- [ ] The simultaneous case converges: 1 local + 1 Jira comment on the same ticket ->\n      2 comments in local AND 2 in Jira (no duplicates, no echo re-import).\n- [ ] Locally-originated comments (carrying the echo marker / matching jira_comment_id)\n      are NOT re-imported.\n- [ ] `inbound_differ ... with_comments` reflects real Jira-side comments (no longer\n      structurally 0 when Jira-side comments exist).\n- [ ] RED->GREEN test: a Jira-origin comment yields an inbound add; an echo does not.","id":"0ee6-58b5-f9bf-4531","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":["jira-sync","reconciler","comments","inbound"],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"Inbound comment sync broken: Jira-side comments never mirror to local (inbound differ has no comment data)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782438825888812001,"uuid":"62f73a36-429a-49a5-9747-62b531bbab4f"}